sparc: add .register pseudo-op declarations for global registers in getcontext.S
Newer binutils require .register directives when using global registers
%%g2 and %%g3 in SPARC assembly. Add the declarations before ENTRY to
avoid "detected global register use not covered by .register pseudo-op"
errors on sparc64 (lines 49-50 of getcontext.S).
